# Path configuration

Could be relative or absolute from the site root.

Absolute:
     var api = minus5.api({
         paths: {
             api: '/api',
         }
     });
if the site root is http://site.com/my/app/index.html
api path will be http://site.com/api


Relative:
     var api = minus5.api({
         paths: {
             api: 'api',
         }
     });
if the site root is http://site.com/my/app/index.html
api path will be http://site.com/my/app/api
